---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="ERP Integration Chihuahua — Connect Your CRM, ERP & Operations Systems | Facware"
  description="Stop reconciling data between systems manually. Facware builds ERP, CRM, and warehouse integrations for mid-market businesses in Chihuahua and the US Southwest — 40%+ reduction in manual ops, fixed scope."
  canonicalURL="https://facware.com/services/erp-integration.html"
  ogDescription="ERP and CRM integration for mid-market operations in Mexico and the US Southwest. Fixed scope, measurable outcome. Built by Facware."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Service",
      "name": "ERP Integration & System Data Connectivity",
      "description": "We connect ERP, CRM, warehouse, and financial systems so mid-market businesses in Mexico and the US Southwest eliminate manual data reconciliation and reduce operational overhead by 40%+.",
      "provider": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "name": "Facware",
        "url": "https://facware.com"
      },
      "areaServed": ["Chihuahua, Mexico", "US Southwest"],
      "serviceType": "ERP Integration",
      "url": "https://facware.com/services/erp-integration.html"
    }
    </script>
  </Fragment>

  <!-- PAGE HERO -->
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <i class="fas fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:10px"></i>
        <a href="/#facware_services">Services</a>
        <i class="fas fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:10px"></i>
        <span aria-current="page">ERP Integration</span>
      </nav>
      <h1>ERP Integration & Data Connectivity for Mid-Market Operations</h1>
      <p>Your ERP, CRM, and warehouse systems should share data automatically — not through weekly exports and manual reconciliation. We build the integrations that make that happen, with a defined outcome before we write a line of code.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PROBLEM -->
  <section class="section" id="problem" aria-labelledby="problem-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">The Integration Tax</p>
        <h2 id="problem-heading">What disconnected systems are actually costing you</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Most mid-market operations run 3–6 systems that were never designed to talk to each other. The gap between them is filled by people.</p>
      </header>
      <div class="cards-grid cards-3">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Weekly reconciliation cycles</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Finance exports from ERP. Ops copies into a spreadsheet. Sales updates the CRM by hand. Every week, someone spends 6–10 hours making sure the numbers match — and they still don't, not quite.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Decisions made on stale data</h3>
          <p class="card-text">When your warehouse system and your ERP are always 24 hours behind each other, every purchasing and fulfillment decision is based on yesterday's reality. That gap costs you on overstocks, stockouts, and margin.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Headcount as a workaround</h3>
          <p class="card-text">You've hired people whose entire job is to bridge the gap between two systems that should communicate directly. They're good at it. And they're expensive — at $30K–$80K/year per person who shouldn't have that job.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DELIVERABLES -->
  <section class="section section--gray" id="deliverables" aria-labelledby="deliverables-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">What You Get</p>
        <h2 id="deliverables-heading">A connected stack, not a patchwork</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Every integration engagement is scoped around your specific systems and a defined business outcome — not an open-ended retainer.</p>
      </header>
      <div class="cards-grid cards-2">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">ERP ↔ CRM bidirectional sync</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Customer data, order history, and account status stay consistent across your ERP and CRM in real time. Sales sees current inventory. Finance sees current pipeline. No exports required.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Warehouse & inventory automation</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Purchase orders, fulfillment status, and inventory levels flow automatically between your WMS and ERP. Receiving updates the system immediately. Shipments trigger downstream notifications without a human in the loop.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Financial system reconciliation</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Invoices, payments, and GL entries move between your operational systems and accounting platform automatically — eliminating end-of-month reconciliation sprints and the errors that come with them.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Custom API & webhook development</h3>
          <p class="card-text">If your systems don't have native connectors, we build them. REST APIs, webhook handlers, event-driven pipelines — whatever the architecture requires to make your tools communicate reliably.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROCESS -->
  <section class="section" id="process" aria-labelledby="process-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">How It Works</p>
        <h2 id="process-heading">From integration gap to production in 3 steps</h2>
      </header>
      <ol class="steps-grid" role="list">
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">01</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3 class="step-title">Systems Audit <span class="badge-free">(Free)</span></h3>
            <p>We map your current stack, document every manual handoff, and quantify the labor cost of each integration gap. You leave with a prioritized list of what to connect first — with projected ROI for each.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">02</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3 class="step-title">Fixed-Scope Integration Proposal</h3>
            <p>We define exactly which systems we're connecting, what data flows, what the business rule logic is, and what success looks like. One price. One timeline. No change orders for scope we agreed on at the start.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">03</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3 class="step-title">Build, Test & Stabilize</h3>
            <p>We build the integration, run it in parallel with your current process, validate data integrity, then cut over. Post-launch monitoring included through 30-day stabilization.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROOF METRICS -->
  <section class="section section--gray" aria-label="Integration results">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="results-grid">
        <div class="results-content">
          <p class="section-eyebrow">What clients see after integration</p>
          <h2>The reconciliation work disappears. The margin doesn't.</h2>
          <ul class="results-list" role="list">
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>40%+ reduction</strong> in manual operational hours after integration go-live</span></li>
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>Eliminated</strong> end-of-month reconciliation cycles for multiple clients</span></li>
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>Real-time data</strong> across ERP, CRM, and warehouse — decisions based on current state</span></li>
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>Fixed price</strong> — every integration is scoped and priced before we start building</span></li>
          </ul>
          <a href="/contact.html#contact-form" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top:8px">Get a free systems audit &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <div class="results-image">
          <img src="/assets/images/facware/resources_facware.png" alt="ERP integration results" loading="lazy" width="600" height="450">
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RELATED SERVICES -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="related-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">Related Services</p>
        <h2 id="related-heading">Often paired with ERP integration</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="cards-grid cards-3">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title"><a href="/services/process-automation.html" class="link-primary">Process Automation</a></h3>
          <p class="card-text">Once your systems share data, the next step is eliminating the manual approvals and triggers that still require human action. We automate those workflows on top of your new integration layer.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title"><a href="/services/custom-software-development.html" class="link-primary">Custom Software Development</a></h3>
          <p class="card-text">When off-the-shelf connectors don't cover your exact business logic, we build purpose-built software that handles your integration requirements precisely.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title"><a href="/services/it-consulting.html" class="link-primary">IT Consulting</a></h3>
          <p class="card-text">Not sure where to start? We audit your stack, map your bottlenecks, and give you a prioritized roadmap — so you're investing in the integrations with the highest ROI first.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA BAND -->
  <section class="cta-band" aria-labelledby="cta-band-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 id="cta-band-heading">Ready to eliminate your integration tax?</h2>
      <p>30-minute operations assessment. No pitch deck. We map your stack, identify the gaps, and tell you exactly what it would cost to fix them — before you commit to anything.</p>
      <a href="/contact.html#contact-form" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Book your free assessment &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .cta-band {
    background: var(--primary);
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: clamp(56px, 8vw, 80px) 24px;
  }
  .cta-band h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: #fff;
  }
  .cta-band p {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto 32px;
    opacity: 0.9;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
  .btn-lg {
    padding: 14px 36px;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
</style>
